 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Computerized Maintenance Management Software Engineer Toyota 8,345 reviews Georgetown, KY 40324 Toyota 8,345 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Who We Are 
Collaborative. Respectful. A place to dream and do. These are just a few words that describe what life is like at Toyota. As one of the world's most admired brands, Toyota is growing and leading the future of mobility through innovative, high-quality solutions designed to enhance lives and delight those we serve. We're looking for diverse, talented team members who want to Dream. Do. Grow. with us.
 Who We're Looking For 
Toyota's IT Experience (ITx) Manufacturing group is looking for a passionate, technical, and highly motivated experienced manager to lead the Plant Maintenance Experience. 
The primary responsibility of this role is to deliver exceptional applications & user experiences through collaboration with company customers, ITx colleagues, business partners, and other stakeholders and demonstrate strong initiative, relationship building, and influential communication skills while applying Toyota Way principles. 
Reporting to the Manager of the Maintenance & Spare Parts Experience, this person will work with Production Engineering and the Regional Maintenance organization to develop and deliver world-class tools supporting all manufacturing plant equipment across North America and will also be instrumental in expanding to 100k+ equipment sensors over the next 3 years supporting Digital Factory / Industry 4.0. 
What You'll Be Doing
 Lead our Maintenance IT Experience team to understand/assess changing business needs while considering technology and business impact. 
 Effectively articulate and communicate business alternatives to a variety of audiences across the business and ITx leadership.
 
 Collaborate across all North American Production Engineering, Regional Maintenance cross-functional team (SOAR), Manufacturing plants, & TMNA enterprise ITx groups to build consensus on decisions.
 
 Continual focus on new technologies, platforms, strategies, and solutions for the future based on technical and economic feasibility.
 
 Work with Strategic vendor partners like IBM, SAP, TRM, Infosys, and others to progress the application rationalization & cloud modernization plan by developing strategic roadmaps and benchmarking both internally and externally.
 
 Develop & deploy Predictive Maintenance (PdM) internal Enterprise solution integrating Equipment Data collection / Sensors (Heat, Vibration, Cycle times), Machine Learning / AI models, Mobile application, notifications, and integration with Maximo. These complex applications play an increasing role in our OneToyota and North America Global Best Manufacturing Strategy. 
 Deliver high visibility projects and new capabilities on an Enterprise Asset Management Platform (Maximo) supporting 13 Manufacturing Plants and over 5000 end-users following Scrum / Agile practice.
 
 Strong management framework to effectively lead a large team (organize, develop & exceed) and manage financials (forecasting, tracking, and variances) for all activities. 
 Active leadership/engagement in daily operations by leading problem and incident management, including ticket monitoring, health checks, and escalations.
 
 Lead regular reviews of the portfolio(s) to identify opportunities for improvement in the areas of stability, performance, and complexity reduction.
 
 Encourage & coach both the IT and Business team in the scrum / agile framework to deliver even better products and services. 
What You Bring
 A bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Management Information Systems or related discipline, or equivalent work experience. 
 A progressive demonstrated functional work experience. 
 Experience with team leadership / supervisory. 
 High-level communication skills to influence and persuade others. 
 Strong written and verbal communication skills with the ability to create and present concepts to make recommendations to management. 
 Hands-on Application Development experience.
 
 Knowledge and experience with progressive technology solutions, including DevOps, AWS Cloud Computing, Micro-Services, Intelligent Automation, Big Data, and Analytics.
 
 Experience managing enterprise applications with large user populations. 
Added Bonus If You Have
 Detailed knowledge and experience with technologies and methodologies within the Manufacturing area. 
 Master's Degree. 
 SAP and/or Maximo knowledge/experience.
 
 Knowledgeable in SOX controls and associated audit procedures. 
Location / Travel Position will be based in Georgetown, KY, at the Production Engineering and Manufacturing Center (PEMC). 
 Monthly travel to North American Manufacturing Plants and/or Corporate Headquarters in Plano, TX should be expected. 
